On StAC I can see "Administration" item in my user menu but when I click on it I get ACCESS DENIED page. It is because I am administrator of JIRA Studio project but not administrator of StAC. Currently the code that decided whether to display Administration menu does this:
{code}
map.put("isAdministrator", studioNavbarInformation.getStudioPermissions().hasAdministratorPermission() || studioNavbarInformation.getStudioPermissions().hasProjectAdministrationPermission());
{code}

I think we should remove {{||}} {{studioNavbarInformation.getStudioPermissions().hasProjectAdministrationPermission()}} part

In Bamboo administration -> 'Elastic Bamboo' -> 'Instances' click on an active instance (e.g. Instance i-3fb64f55).

In the section "SSH Access" it will have instructions like:

{quote}
You can SSH into this instance in the EC2. To do this, simply execute the following command from the bamboo server home directory. You can also download the SSH private key file from here and use the private key to access the EC2 instance.
{noformat}
ssh -i /data/jirastudio/bamboo/home/xml-data/configuration/elasticbamboo.pk  root@ec2-75-101-183-76.compute-1.amazonaws.com
{noformat}
{quote}

However, this is misleading because no customer can SSH into their Studio instance to run this command. It should simply instruct them to download the file and SSH to the instance using the downloaded key.

The same goes for the 'Accessing Logs' section below it.

I find myself increasingly wanting to set a fix for version when I resolve issues via commit commands.  Suggest something like this:

{noformat}
ABC-123 #resolve #fixfor 2.5
{noformat}
